  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "When I record my face and the video I am reacting to on the same computer, the audio plays in the background of webcam footage. How do I fix it?",
  "response": "If you're experiencing audio playback from the video in the background of your webcam footage, there are a few ways to fix this issue. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Use Headphones:**\n   - Wear headphones while recording. This way, the audio from the video won't be picked up by your computer's microphone.\n\n2. **Dedicated Software:**\n   - Use recording software that allows you to set different audio sources. Software like OBS Studio, Camtasia, or Bandicam can help with this. In these programs, you can choose to record desktop audio separately from your microphone audio.\n\n3. **Separate Audio Tracks:**\n   - If you're using software like OBS Studio, you can set up separate audio tracks. This way, the desktop audio (video audio) and microphone audio (your voice) are recorded on different tracks. This makes it easier to edit them separately later on.\n\n4. **Mute Audio During Recording:**\n   - If your reaction doesn't need the audio content while recording, mute the audio of the video during the recording process. This can often be done by adjusting audio settings within your video player or recording software.\n\n5. **Post-production Editing:**\n   - Use video editing software to remove or adjust the audio levels after recording. If the audio tracks are combined, software like Adobe Premiere Pro, Final Cut Pro, or even free software like Audacity can help isolate and adjust audio levels.\n\n6. **Microphone Settings:**\n   - Adjust the sensitivity and settings of your microphone to ensure it picks up less background noise. Many microphones and audio interfaces come with software to tweak their settings.\n\nHere\u2019s a quick guide on how to set up OBS Studio for separate audio tracks:\n\n- **Download and Install OBS Studio.**\n- **Add Sources:** Click on the \"+\" sign under \"Sources\" to add your display capture (for the video you\u2019re reacting to) and video capture device (for your webcam).\n- **Adjust Audio Settings:** In the Audio Mixer, you\u2019ll see separate sliders for your desktop audio and microphone. You can lower the desktop audio here to avoid overlap.\n- **Advanced Audio Properties:** Click the gear icon next to the Audio Mixer and select \"Advanced Audio Properties.\" Here, you can assign different audio sources to separate tracks.\n- **Recording Settings:** Go to \"Settings\" > \"Output\" > \"Recording.\" Ensure \"Audio Tracks\" has multiple tracks selected (e.g., Track 1 for mic audio, Track 2 for desktop audio).\n- **Start Recording:** When you record, OBS will create a file with multiple audio tracks.\n\nFollowing these steps should help you avoid having the video's audio playing in the background of your webcam footage, allowing for a cleaner and more professional recording.",
